apartment_name: Good for sharing furnished 2 double bedrooms apartment with terrace
apartment_description:
FOR RENT: 110m2 2br stylish modern apartment in Bos en Lommer
Rent: 2150,- (excl. utilities, annual city tax).
Deposit: required and refundable
HIGHLIGHTS
Fully furnished with premium brands (Bolia, Fest) Fully furnished kitchen with brand name appliances, extra freezer, dishwasher and pantry
Two bedrooms: King size bed (2x2m) and queen-size (1.6x2m) 8th floor with lift, excellent view, year-round sunlight
Double-paned windows, great insolation, large balcony
Easy access tram, bus, metro and highway
Quiet residential neighborhood with families, next to canals and football club
NEIGHBORHOOD
Albert Heijn, Vormar, Dirk, Aldi Erasmuspark De School (trendy restaurant, cafe, gym, club) Gym with swimming pool Buurman en Buurman artisanal pizza OLVG West hospital
CONDITIONS
Prefer quiet, neat working professionals. No smoking inside. No pets allowed.
VIEWING
Please get in touch with a self intro. Viewing available as soon as we receive your profiles and compositions.

Beautiful new huge 3 bedrooms house with roof terrace in Zaandam
apartment_description:
Beautiful, fully furnished luxury 4-rooms family home with a lovely spacious sunny roof terrace located in a well-maintained modern house. This spacious, bright house has three floors and is located in a very quiet and safe residential area and is within walking distance of the center and the railway station. Short distance from a.o. Amsterdam and Haarlem, to Amsterdam it is 15 minutes by car.
Layout:
Ground floor: entrance, spacious hall with space for bicycles, stairs to
First floor: spacious bright living room with a beautiful view of the green area at the rear. Open modern kitchen with all appliances with a beautiful view of the water (the river Zaan).
Second floor: landing, 2 spacious bedrooms and a modern bathroom
bath, separate shower, sink and toilet.
Third floor: spacious bedroom with sunny and very spacious roof terrace (25 m2) with a beautiful.
Conditions:
- Suitable for a family household of maximum 4/5 persons household, no students, no group-rental. Sharing by max 2 non family individuals.
- 1 month deposit and refundable.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
- Minimum 12 months contract.
- Rent is 2050,- exclusive utilities.
- 1 month viewing rights at termination off the contract
- Pets are not allowed.
- No smoking and no changes can be made to the property (painting, drilling etc) without the written consent of the landlord.

apartment_name: Furnished De Pijp apartment with 2 double bedrooms jacuzzi and garden
apartment_description:
This fully furnished apartment is located in one of the best areas of Amsterdam, the Old-South. It is on walking distance of the Centre and the area is referred to as ‘the Pijp’ (Quartier Latin), famous for it’s large daily Albert Cuyp market, numerous bars & restaurants. All nice locations in and around the centre of town are on walking or cycle distance.
Lay-out:
Entrance hallway with separate toilet, staircase and entrance to the large living. In front of the living we find a kitchen and dining area, this kitchen of course, comes fully equipped. At the back we have the cosy living with garden view and entrance to the very large and deep garden! In the middle of town you will enjoy this as a heaven of rest and relaxation. In the garden there is even a good size shed, to store the BBQ and Sunbeds!
Upstairs there are two good size bedrooms, at the back of the house there is a large master bedroom complete with balcony and walking closet. In the middle of the two rooms we find the bathroom, this is the ultimo kick for people who like bathing. This bathroom features no only a tub with bubble function, but you have a complete massage shower cabin as well! Just great after a hard day’s work! The apartment can be delivered furnished or semi-furnished, the landlord is flexible to discuss all options.
This area is served by tram lines: 3,4,6,7,12,16,24 and 25.
Great apartment on great location! All-in-all a unique opportunity to get a taste of Amsterdam living in a great part of town with everything you need close by.
- Rent is 2250,- exclusive utilities.
- Refundable deposit required.
- Registration with the city hall is mandatory.

Nicely furnished 2 bedrooms apartment beside Oosterpark
apartment_description:
This well-kept three-rooms apartment of approximately 65m2 on the second floor is located in the very popular Boerhaavebuurt / Oosterparkbuurt near the Oosterpark. It has two bedrooms, two balconies, a luxurious bathroom and a spacious living room with a beautiful open kitchen.
Layout:
The apartment can be reached via the common wide staircase.
Second floor: entrance to hall with access to all rooms. Light and spacious living room with double doors to the balcony at the front. In the living room there is a modern, open kitchen in high gloss white with various built-in appliances such as a 5-burners stove with wok burner, combi-oven/microwave, dishwasher, refrigerator, freezer and hood. Adjacent to the kitchen is the wide balcony on the south with nice views of green. There is a bedroom at the front. At the rear is the spacious master bedroom where double doors also provide access to the balcony. The spacious, nicely finished bathroom is located in the extension where the windows on two sides provide a lotvof natural light. There is a bath with hand shower, furniture with double sink, walk-in shower with rain shower and design radiator. Further through the hall a separate toilet with fountain and a storage cupboard with washing machine and dryer. In the apartment is a wide oak slate parquetcfloor.
Surroundings:
The street is located invthe eastern part of the city and adjacentvto the Oosterpark. Near is the cozy Weesperzijde with fine restaurants such as Girassol and De Ysbreker. The Amstel is around the corner for runners, cyclists and rowers. The convenient location in one of the most central places of East ensures quick access to the other nice cafes/restaurants that the neighborhood has to offer. Think of: Bar Bukowski, Louie Louie, Loetje Oost, The Breakfast Club, Volkshotel and Hotel Arena (with terraces located at the park). You can shop at the Dappermarkt or at the nearby Oosterpoort shopping center. Also the popular neighborhood De Pijp with its many restaurants, cozy cafes, shops andvthe Albert Cuyp market can be reached in a few minutes by bike. The apartment is conveniently located to the S100 and S112 roads and has a good connection with public transport (tram 1, 3 and 7, Amstel station, Muiderpoort station and metro stations Weesperplein and Wibautstraat).
Particularities:
- Not for sharing by colleagues.
- Rent is 1750,- including service costs and excluding g/w/e and internet
- Refundable deposit required
- Registration with the city hall is mandatory
- Living area: 65 m2
- Balconies: total: 6 m2
- Double glass

Huge 185 m2 penthouse 3 beds 2 baths terrace and garage
apartment_description:
Photos of the interior upon request!
- Can be furnished or unfurnished as well, same price.
- Minimum lease is 1 year, longer possible.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
- Rent is 2500,- exclusive utilities.
Completely furnished 185 m2 duplex penthouse Amsterdam (185 M2) at district Nieuw Sloten.
This is private, modern apartment is completely furnished. The location is extremely practical and efficient for busy people who look for rest and comfort without all the hassle of the centre of Amsterdam. There are no traffic jams and parking problems, while all the positive aspects of the capital (theatre, museums, restaurants and train station) and its historical centre are only 20-30 minutes away.
Apartment:
This completely furnished, penthouse apartment has two floors with an area of 185m2. The living-room (65m2) is extremely nice in its form (also semi-oval) with windows all around at the west side and access to the terrace. In the middle an opening over two levels, giving it as special spaciousness. The kitchen is modern and supplied with all facilities (refrigerator, microwave & oven and, of course, all other smaller kitchen appliances). From the terrace a nice view over the neighbourhood and its trees and a little modern canal. At the second floor master bedroom with a walk-in closet and the bathroom adjacent. Down the corridor two other bedrooms. The other bathrooms with shower cabin. There is are sufficient separate storage closets in the corridor at the second floor. At every level there is a separate toilet. All basic facilities are available, as well as wired highspeed connections in every room as well as WIFI and highspeed connection for smartTV. Washing machine and dryer in separate space. The character and atmosphere of the apartment is one of spaciousness and openness.
Neighbourhood:
The neighbourhood (Nieuw Sloten) is strategically extremely well located in relation to the main highways around Amsterdam. All (A10-A4-A9-A1) are quickly within reach through the south-ring A10 of Amsterdam, which is only 400 meters away. This part of the ring is named the "south-axis" and is meant to be the "golden belt for offices" in Amsterdam and Holland. Schiphol airport (national airport) is very close (only 5 minutes by car), although the noise of the airplanes doesn't play a significant role due to the advantageous directions of the more distant runways.
The apartment "block" (which isn't a "block" but a separate somewhat oval-shaped building with seven floors and three penthouses) is situated in the heart of this modern, quiet and green neighbourhood with park at it's border. Spacious green, trees and a nice pond surround the building. Parking is free and always possible, which is a miracle in the city of Amsterdam. The tram (Nr. 2) stops almost in front of the building and brings you to the historical region and the heart of the city (including Central Train Station) within 20-30 minutes. Basic shops (supermarket, liquor store, drugstore, hairdresser, florist etc.) are all around the corner around the local square.
Partial list of amenities:
- Fast-speed wireless computer connection for continuous internet
- Fully furnished bedrooms, living and dining rooms.
- Fully Equipped Kitchen
- Central heating.
- 25" Color TV .
- Washer, dryer & iron, linens and towels.
- Optional reserved parking.

apartment_name: Furnished 2 double bedrooms apartment in Amstelveen
apartment_description:
Available as of June 1st for at least 1 year, longer preferred. Amstelveen area.
Furnished 2-bedrooms apartment is located on the second floor of a well-maintained apartment complex. From the hall of the apartment there is access to the living room. The living room is bright thanks to the large windows at the rear. The balcony is accessible from the living room and is facing southeast. The apartment has two bedrooms. The master bedroom has a double bed. The second bedroom also has a double bed. Both bedrooms have built-in wardrobe space. The closed kitchen is equipped with all comforts such as a fridge with freezer, 5-burner stove and combi-oven. The bathroom is accessible from the kitchen and is equipped with a walk-in shower, sink, washing machine and dryer. In addition, there is a separate toilet in the apartment. The apartment complex is located in the residential area of Keizer Karelpark with lots of greenery and water features. In the immediate vicinity you will find shops on the Van der Hooplaan, a large Albert Heijn in Bovenkerk, the Groenhof shopping center, sports facilities on the Sportlaan, De Poel recreational lake and the Amsterdamse Bos. Public transport stops for tram 5, 51 and bus lines 347, 348 and 357 are within walking distance of the apartment. The roads to the A10 and A9 are quickly and easily accessible. The International School is within walking distance. You can park your car free of charge in the immediate vicinity.
Conditions:
- per June 1st for at least 1 year, longer preferred.
- rent is 1650.- INCLUDING UTILITIES.
- one month refundable deposit required.
- registration with the city hall is compulsory.

Sharing allowed cozy 2 double bedrooms downtown apartment
apartment_description:
No agency fee required nor hidden costs for the tenants.
This fully renovated apartment is located on the third floor of a characteristic building on the Nieuwezijds Voorburgwal, in the heart of the lively city center. The house is stylishly furnished and ideal for a couple, single or sharing by 2 people.
Layout: Via the central entrance and the general staircase you reach the front door of the apartment on the third floor. living room with open kitchen. The kitchen is equipped with various built-in appliances, including a refrigerator, freezer, combi oven and dishwasher. Two spacious bedrooms, both with a double bed and a large closet. Modern bathroom with a bathtub and a separate walk-in shower, a sink unit and a design radiator. The washer and dryer are located in a separate room and there is a separate toilet room.
In the immediate vicinity you will find numerous restaurants and cozy cafes. You can do your shopping around the corner on the Nieuwe Dijk and the famous Kalverstraat. A very large Albert Heijn supermarket is located in the street for your daily shopping.
This area is served by several tram lines and bus lines. It’s a 10 minute walk to central station or one stop by tram. 2 minutes to Dam square and next to Magna Plaza shopping center.
Size: 60m2
Bedrooms: 2
Bathroom with bathtub & separate shower
Furnished: Yes
Pets: No
Separate toilet
Available: Now
Price: 1600,- exclusive utilities
Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
The apartment has an energy label A.
In short, a lovely apartment right in the center of Amsterdam.

Brand new 2 bedrooms duplex house with garden + free parking
apartment_description:
Can be both furnished or unfurnished as well. Furnished will cost slightly above the asking price.
Available as of May 1st for at least 1 year, longer preferred.
Located in Amsterdam Noord at the newly renovated and upcoming NDSM Area.
- Rent is 1650,- exclusive utilities.
- Refundable deposit required equal to two months rent.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
Sustainability was a high priority in the construction of this house. HR Glass and underfloor heating ensure that energy costs are kept low.
The ‘NDSM werf’ is within walking distance where you will find a variety of hotspots like Pllekk, De IJkantine , Cafe Noorderlicht. For shopping you have the IJhallen just around the corner.
The ‘NDSM Werf ‘ is characterized by sheds and cranes and is an inspiring environment for many creatives. With the ferry you are within less than 10 minutes at the Central Station. From this point the Haarlemmerdijk and Jordaan are within Walking distance.
Lay out:
Entrance, toilet with wash basin, Spacious living room including large high windows. The 'L form' kitchen in the corner of the living area is fully equipped with several appliances, such as a refrigerator, combination oven/microwave, induction cooker, dish washer and cooker hood (SMEG). From the living room you reach the garden and in the garden you will find a detached shed.
Stairs leading to the first floor: on this floor you will find two bedrooms and a separate room for the washer / dryer. The bathroom has a large walk-in shower.
In this area the parking is still free.
Features:
- Brand new: Delivered in 2019
- Light
- Parking is free
- Energy efficient home
- Solar Panels

Available now unfurnished 1 bedroom apartment with garden
apartment_description:
Immediately available for at least 1 year, longer preferred.
No agency fee required nor hidden costs for the tenants.
This spacious UN-Furnished 1 bedroom apartment with garden is located in a popular area of Amterdam called De Baarsjes in Old West. Very close to the vibrant Mercatorplein which offers lots of shops, bars and restaurants. Erasmuspark is just s few blocks away. It's a 60 m2 apartment plus the garden.
The living room has lots of light with a view of the canal. The separate kitchen has all appliances and is in an excellent condition.
The spacious bedroom is located at the rear with access to the garden. In the back of the garden is a shed to store your garden furniture over the winter months.

apartment_description:
Furnished or unfurnished as well, spacious and recently renovated villa with large garden (facing South) in Abcoude nearby Amsterdam. The town center is a 5-minutes walk.
Living area app. 200m2.
There is space for 3 cars. One on the driveway, two on the road. (no license needed).
Layout:
Entrance hall with toilet, utility room with kitchenette. Large open plan kitchen with marble counter tops, all appliances (Siemens) and large cooking "island". Very large and bright living room with cozy fireplace. Huge glass wall at the rear side what makes the living very bright. Sliding doors to spacious backyard with patio, build in BBQ and fountain.
First floor: landing, master bedroom with balcony, spacious walk-in closet and luxurious bathroom with double shower, double sink, floor heating, built-in TV and jacuzzi. Second bedroom, second bathroom with shower and a sink, third bedroom. Child rose bedroom can be painted in wanted color.
Spacious attic, which could be used as a large (4th) bedroom, access to boiler room.
Both furnished and unfurnished rentals.
Costs:
* Rent is 3950,- excluding bills.
* Two months refundable deposit required.
Details:
* Ground floor has beautiful stone flooring. The first and second floors got new carpeting.
* Large private garden.
* Excellent condition.
* The railway station, library, public elementary school, swimming pool and a grocery store are all within a few minutes walking distance.

Unfurnished luxury duplex house with 5 bedrooms garden and parking
apartment_description:
Unfurnished semi-detached, 5 bedrooms villa (200m sqm) hanging above an eco-lake and located in a quiet green area in Amsterdam-West. (Osdorp - De Aker).
Ground floor :
Spacious hall with cloakroom and toilet. Stairs to the upper and lower floors. Very bright and spacious living room with windows and sliding doors to the balcony. Half open plan kitchen. Kitchen unit comes with ceramic hob, extractor, combi oven & microwave, dishwasher, refrigerator and freezer. Lots of cupboard space and drawers.
On this floor is an oak wooden floor and light curtains hang over the windows.
Downstairs / basement floor:
Landing with stairs cupboard. Bed / study room with door to the terrace built in the water. Storage / shed with door to street.
Top floor:
Landing with toilet and access to all 4 bedrooms. (9, 12, 14 and 18m2). Two bedrooms fitted wardrobes. Bathroom with 2 sinks, bath, separate shower and towel radiator. Laundry room with washing machine and dryer.
On this floor is a wooden floor.
The area in which this architect-designed villa is located is special. The dead-end street is surrounded by water. From the living room you look on one side against the ring canal of Badhoevedorp and on the other side you look out over the eco lake.
The house is within walking distance of tram 1 and shopping centre '' De Dukaat '', near exit roads A9 and A10, and 10 minutes from Schiphol Airport.
Parking is free in the neighbourhood and can be parked at your own parking space.
Additional information:
- Available immediately.
- Rent is 2800,- excl. G-W-E-T. V-Internet and Municipality Taxes.
- Refundable deposit required.

apartment_name: Huge furnished 3 bedrooms ground floor duplex with a big garden
apartment_description:
Well maintained and spacious ground floor apartment of 141 m² with a garden of no less than 113 m² and 3 good bedrooms. The house is furnished and is divided over two floors; the ground floor consisting of the living area and the basement consisting of the sleeping area.
A lovely house that you can directly move into!
Layout:
The living room has both front and rear windows making it very light in the house. The kitchen and living room both offer access to the spacious garden. The garden is west facing and has a barn. The kitchen was renovated in 2018 and has all modern conveniences such as: 6-burner stove, oven, microwave, dishwasher and fridge-freezer. Next to the living room there is an extra room which is perfect as a work space. The ground floor also has a toilet.
The basement has 3 good bedrooms, a walk-in closet, bathroom with bath, separate shower, double sink, toilet and washing machine. Also, the basement has a large storage space.
Rental details:
- Furnished
- Minimum rental period 1 year
- Maximum rental period 2 years
- Rent ia 2650,- per month excl. g/w/l (no brokers or contact costs due)
- Deposit is 2650,-
- Pets allowed in consultation
Location:
Located in the middle of the popular Baarsjes between the Admiraal de Ruijterweg and the Willem de Zwijgerlaan, with many shops, supermarkets, the Ten Katemarkt and De Hallen just a stone's throw away. There are also parks nearby, such as the Erasmuspark and Rembrandtpark. Cozy cafes and nice restaurants such as Bar Kauffman, Zurich, Edel, Spijkervet and Cook are also nearby. By bike you are within 10 minutes in the Jordaan and 15 minutes from the Centre. Public transport stops (tram 12, 13, 14 and bus 18) are just around the corner (Admiral de Ruijterweg/Jan van Galenstraat) and offer direct, fast connections to both CS and Sloterdijk. By car you can reach the A10 ring road within five minutes. The neighbourhood is good for families, with many day care centres and primary schools within walking distance. In all aspects a top location!

Gorgeous De Pijp duplex with 3 bedrooms and roof terrace
apartment_description:
Very nice and spacious apartment with three bedrooms, living room with open kitchen, balcony with afternoon/evening sun and a rooftop terrace. The apartment is located in a quiet street in the nicest part of the Pijp area, close to several shops and groceries, the Museumplein, the daily Albert Cuyp market and a big variety of bars and restaurants. The M52 metroline (stop on a 100m distance) has a fast and direct connection to Amsterdam Central Station and Amsterdam Zuid station (where you can take the train to Schiphol Airport).
Details:
- Fully furnished
- Recently refurbished
- Balcony and large rooftop terrace
- Rental price is 2950,- excl. utilities costs
- Total living space is 111m2
- 2 large bedrooms, and 1 smaller bedroom
- Two months rent as deposit
- Available for long term (maximum 2 years)

Spacious furnished 1 bedroom apartment near Vondelpark
apartment_description:
Immediately available for at least 1 year, longer preferred.
Very sunny and spacious one bedroom-apartment of about 64 m2 in Amsterdam residential center Oud-West.
Fully furnished. 1 bedroom, 1 spacious living room and separate fully equipped kitchen, 1 bathroom and 1 separate toilet room. In the bathroom is a bathtub and a washing machine. 2 balconies are accessible from the living room and from the kitchen and bedroom. The balcony from the kitchen/bedroom is facing big trees. The apartment is light and sunny. 3rd floor.
In an arm-length from Kinkerstraat and very close to the shopping street and outdoor market. 5 min walk to Vondelpark, 10 min by tram to Central Station. Tram 17 and 7 stop in 1 minute walking distance from the house.
Specifics:
- This apartment is ideal for a couple or on your own.
- Energy category B, which makes service bills quite low.
- Rent is 1500,- excluding utilities (internet/water/electricity/gas)
- Deposit of 1 month and refundable.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
- We’re looking for a trustworthy person or couple who are looking for a beautiful place to live.
- The apartment is ready for viewings!

Beautiful furnished 2 bedrooms duplex with roof terrace + Free parking
apartment_description:
For at least 1 year but longer is preferred. Located in Osdorp nearby Ecuplein shopping centre and tram line 1. Just 15 minutes to Lelylaan station and Schiphol airport. It consists of a newly renovated two storey apartment with a huge sunny living room, separate fully equipped kitchen, storage room, toilet, great bathroom, 2 well sized bedrooms and a roof terrace. Schools are just a few blocks away. Free parking in front of the door!
Layout
You enter the house via a staircase: reception hall, where the meter cupboard and staircase are located. There is a laminate floor in the hall. The floors were replaced in 2018 and are in very good condition. The living room is a beautiful, light space with large windows. The living room has a modern open kitchen (2014) with all conceivable built-in appliances such as a 5-burner hob, dishwasher, extractor hood, fridge and oven. . At the front of the house is the open kitchen, which has a pleasant fresh look thanks to the high-gloss white kitchen cupboard. 1st floor: The landing on the first floor gives access to two large bedrooms and the bathroom. The landing is also equipped with a laminate floor, which continues beautifully into the bedrooms. The bedroom at the rear of the house also has access to the roof terrace (west). The bathroom has luxury finishes and bathroom furniture. including a walk-in shower, and a washbasin with single washbasin and mirror cabinet. The bathroom has mechanical ventilation for sufficient air supply. The washing machine connection and central heating system are neatly concealed in a built-in cupboard on the landing.
Conditions:
- For at least 1 year but longer is preferred.
- rent is 1700,- exclusive utilities.
- refundable deposit required.
- registration with the city hall is compulsory.

Unfurnished renovated 3 bedrooms apartment in Amsterdam Noord
apartment_description:
Please read full description before applying!
No agency fee required nor hidden costs for the tenants!
Summary:
For rent a well laid out 4 room apartment on 3rd floor. The apartment was completely renovated two years ago. Read the full description below. Apartment is in a nice green neighborhood (Loodskotterhof) with many children. Park is around the corner, North South line 7 minutes by bike. Separate storage room on the ground floor.
For who?
Renting for a longer period is preferred. Property is suitable for children. Child-friendly porch. Ideal for (working) couple. Home dividers up to 2 persons possible. Let me know which people rent it and mention your phonenumber.
Characteristics:
Available from 1st April 2021. (a little) later in consultation.
Price 1750,- per month
Heating costs 50, - per month via block heating
Apartment fully electric.
No gas required, so no standing charge.
1 month deposit
Description:
Recently renovated apartment in Amsterdam Noord. This 4-room apartment is located on the 3rd floor of a neat apartment complex. Equipped with a spacious living room, modern kitchen with adjoining dining room, 3 bedrooms and a bathroom. The apartment is located on a green park and has a large south-facing balcony with awning. Parking in front of the door is free. The property has just been completely renovated and is in excellent condition.
Layout:
You enter the apartment in the spacious living room. Through the large windows at the front and rear of the house, the living room is also wonderfully light. In the living room is the (completely renovated) meter cupboard, a cupboard containing a new electric boiler and a washing machine connection and a storage cupboard.
From the dining room you enter the modern kitchen through an open passage. The kitchen has plenty of storage space and a dishwasher. The hall is centrally located in the apartment and gives access to the bedrooms, the bathroom and the toilet. The toilet is in a separate room at the end of the hall and the bathroom has a bathtub and sink.
The apartment has three bedrooms. There is one spacious bedroom at the front of the house. The second bedroom is located at the rear of the house and gives access to the balcony. The smaller third bedroom can serve as a baby room or office.

On the first floor there are 2 bedrooms and the house has 2 bathrooms. 1 on the first and 1 on the second floor. On the second floor there is a very spacious bedroom / hobby room. Another plus of the neighborhood is that you can park for FREE in the street!

Huge apartment near Oosterpark with 2 bedrooms lift and garage
apartment_description:
Can be furnished or unfurnished as well, same price.
Beautifully renovated three-room apartment (living area 114 m²) with a fantastic view over the Singelgracht. The apartment is located on the second floor of apartment complex “Het Torenpunt”, a very beautiful building designed by architect Van Egeraat. The apartment is fully equipped and includes a new luxury open kitchen with various built-in appliances, a spacious living room, two bedrooms, a new separate wc and a new bathroom with double rain shower, double sink and a second wc On the ground floor is an optional private parking space in the parking basement.
Surroundings:
The Mauritskade is located on the edge of the bustling center of Amsterdam. In the immediate vicinity there are numerous facilities. So you are within 10 minutes in the city center and there are several shops, as well as the Dappermarkt in the immediate vicinity. The public transport facilities are excellent. In addition, the sights such as Artis and the tropical museum are within walking distance. For relaxation you can stroll through the Oosterpark or enjoy one of the many catering establishments such as the Biertuin or the Louie Louie. You will also be at the A-10 Ring Road in no time.
Layout:
Ground floor: Central entrance; hall; elevator; parking basement.
Second floor: Entrance; hall; new luxury open kitchen with various built-in appliances; spacious living room; new separate wc with fountain; two bedrooms; internal storage with central heating system, mechanical ventilation box and washing machine connections; new bathroom with double rain shower, double sink and a second wc. There is a beautiful view from the entire apartment!
Details:
– Built in 2002
– Beautifully designed building by architect Van Egeraat
– Fully insulated with three double glazing, among others
– Living area 114 m²
– Fantastic view over the Singelgracht
– Optional parking space in the basement
– The car can already be called from the apartment
- Rent: 2250,- excluding utilities
- Optional private Parking: 255 euro
- Deposit: yes

Furnished 3 bedrooms apartment nearby the Zoo and Nemo Museum
apartment_description:
Available for at
least 1 year, longer possible.
No sharing by more than 2 non family individuals.
Sharing by a officially married couple and a friend is allowed by the city hall.
A well-maintained corner apartment in the center of Amsterdam. The house has 3 bedrooms, separate kitchen, a south-facing balcony and is located in a quiet street with greenery and water around it. Shops, restaurants, museums, recreational facilities and Amsterdam Central Station are in the vicinity.
The many windows allow a great deal of natural light to enter the living room. The adjoining balcony is located on the south and is spacious enough for a table and chairs for an extensive breakfast in the morning. There is a laminate floor throughout the house.
The kitchen is equipped with an induction hob with 4 burners, extractor hood, oven, dishwasher, refrigerator and freezer with three drawers. The balcony can also be reached through the kitchen.
The house has three good-sized bedrooms, which can be reached from the central hall.
The bathroom has a walk-in shower, washbasin with two sinks, radiator and mechanical ventilation. The floor is tiled with beautiful Portuguese tiles.
In addition, the apartment has a separate WC with a fountain, also with a Portuguese tiled floor.
The apartment has a separate laundry room that can accommodate both a washing machine and dryer.
The storage room is located in the basement and is large enough for a number of bicycles.
LOCATION
The apartment is located in a quiet street in the center of Amsterdam. In the area you will find restaurants including Entrepot, Kanteen 25, and De Kop van Oost. In addition, the Haarlemmerstraat, with a wide range of shops, is located +/- 10 minutes. Here you will find various boutiques and specialized shops with clothing, accessories, toys, electronics, books and jewelery, as well as salons, caterers, restaurants and bars (such as restaurant Stout !, cafe Nieuw Amsterdam, Nobo, Pizzeria Lucca Due, Vinnies, Bistrot Neuf ). You will also find the Jordaan, Dam Square, Artis and Hortus Botanicus Amsterdam within 5-10 minutes cycling distance from the house.
The house is easily accessible by both car and public transport. The Central Station is a 10-minute bike ride away. You can take the train, tram and bus here to go to Schiphol or other major cities. By car you are on the A1 or A10 within 10 minutes. Parking is available in the street. For more information about a parking permit (permit area: Centrum 4) you can consult the website of the municipality of Amsterdam.
Registration possible with the city hall is compulsory.
Rent is 1850,- exclusive utilities.
Refundable deposit required.

Looking for a beautifully finished, fully furnished apartment in the middle of the Amsterdam Old West? From now
on, this opportunity can be used; a three rooms apartment with luxury bathroom, kitchen and lots of storage space and s small charming garden at the rear. The house is completely renovated in 2018 with a new kitchen, new bathroom,
which is equipped with underfloor heating, a new floor, new pieces, new paintwork, new lighting and new curtains.
A picture of a house where you can pull in! Furthermore, there are many cupboards and there is a lovely garden on
the South which is very quiet. And all that in the middle of Amsterdam Old West, with the Westerpark and many
restaurants and cafes a few meters away. This is fully enjoyed!
The apartment.
The apartment is located on the ground floor of this charming property. You can reach the house via a stairwell.
Then the entrance and directly to the right bedroom 2 which has fitted wardrobes and an extendable bed. The
bedroom has beautiful, dark window frames which creates a beautiful light show. The living room is very light
through the large windows and also here is very well thought about light and space, the fitted wardrobes walk right
to the kitchen. Light, space, and radiation, you will find it all here. Then an open kitchen from 2018 which is
equipped with a dishwasher, combi-oven with steam function, extractor hood, 4-burner gas stove, an espresso
machine and a concealed washing machine with a dry combination. The bathroom has a shower, sink and toilet, and
is also equipped with mirror and underfloor heating! Then bedroom 1 at the rear of the house which is also
wonderful to close by a sliding door with the same beautiful window frames. Access to the garden, located on the
South so delicious in the sun, quiet and with colorful flowers.
Location.
The Van Hogendorpstraat is located in the Westerparkbuurt / Staatsliedenbuurt, West district. The neighborhood is
very popular and within walking distance of several cozy cafes, restaurants and various shops. For recreation you
can go to the nearby Westerpark. In the vicinity there are several public transport lines and roads to find, making
the accessibility of the home good. The Jordaan and the Central station are about ten minutes by bike. There is
sufficient parking space in the street (parking for a fee and / or through a permit system.

apartment_name: Furnished cozy 1 bedroom apartment nearby Jordaan and Westerpark
apartment_description:
No agency fee required nor hidden costs for the tenants!
This is a charming 1 bedroom furnished apartment of approx 55m2 on the 1st floor of this canal facing building. It is located in a vibrant part of Oud-West. Both the Vondelpark and the Beatrixpark are within in 10mins walking distance (800mtrs)
There are lots bars, restaurant and shops in close proximity to the apartment. Once the lockdown is finished, you can enjoy their hospitality.
The living room has good quality furniture fitted and a west facing French balcony from which there is an unobstructed view of one of the major canals in Amsterdam.
The kitchen is fully equiped with all appliances. The Bathroom features a modern free-standing bathtub, a shower and WC.
There is an additional storage room on the 4th floor of the building. This is also where the laundrymachine is located.
- rent: 1400,- excl utilities
- deposit: 2000,- and refundable.
- registration with the city hall is compulsory.

Furnished house 4 bedrooms 2 bathrooms garage and garden
apartment_description:
Super huge furnished family house with no less than 4 bedrooms in a child-friendly neighborhood with private parking and garden with conservatory!
The location is ideal. By car you are quickly on the Gooiseweg and therefore quickly on the A9, A10 or A2. Within cycling distance of the Bijlmer center with the Amsterdamse Poort, the Arena and the Nelson Mandelapark. A 5-minute walk from the metro stop and then in half an hour on Dam Square.
An ideal living environment!
Layout
This single-family home has the classic and most ideal layout. On the ground floor own parking spot and stone storage unit, when entering a hall with meter cupboard and toilet, a spacious living room with underfloor heating with sliding doors to the garden on the southwest. There is a conservatory with heating so you can sit outside on all days.
The luxurious open kitchen has various equipment including; an American fridge with freezer, dishwasher, oven, microwave, extractor, hob and plenty of cupboard space.
On the first floor you will find three spacious bedrooms and a luxurious bathroom with bath, toilet, shower and sink. On this floor you will also find the washing machine with dryer.
On the second floor there is as a surprise a very spacious bedroom with balcony, walk-in closet, air conditioning and a luxurious bathroom with a toilet, sink and special shower with heat massage.
The house is available immediately and registration is compolsory.
Rent is 2100,- exclusive utilities.
Refundable deposit equal to 2 months rent.

Unfurnished family house 4 bedrooms garage terrace on the water
apartment_description:
This lovely family house is located on the Eastern Docklands.
The 'Oostelijk Havengebied' is the part of Amsterdam that lies in the corner of the IJ and the Amsterdam-Rijnkanaal. At the end of the 19th century, a port area was built to provide space for the increasing overseas trade. The construction of the railway and the Central Station in front of the old harbor in front of the city meant that new locations for harbors were needed. Borneo Island is an artificial peninsula that was built in the 19th century in the Eastern Docklands of Amsterdam.
The Eastern Docklands are known for modern urban construction, striking architecture, spaciousness and of course contact with water. In short, a unique piece of Amsterdam.
You can reach the center or the CS by bike in 15 minutes. Tram 10 or 26 will take you to the center or CS in a short time. With the Oostveer you have a very good connection with Amsterdam Noord. By car you are in the A10 via the Piet Hein tunnel in a few minutes.
Within walking distance you will find the shopping center Brazilie (including Albert Heijn, Jumbo, Estafette and pharmacy), several schools, a caterer, domestic stores like Pol's Potten and Sissy Boy Homeland, gyms, the Lloyd Hotel, Club Panama, HappyHappyJoyJoy.
For water lovers, there is a marina and a sailing school nearby.
Lay-out.
Entrance, hallway with access to separate toilet and garage in the rear, in the front there is a spacious bedroom.
Stairs towards 1st floor.
Spacious modern kitchen-diner in the rear with built-in appliances.
Light and bright living room in the front, with hard wood floor throughout.
Stairs towards 2nd floor, spacious landing.
Master bedroom with walk in closet, third bedroom.
Bathroom with bath, shower, double hand wash basin + separate toilet.
Stairs towards top floor, guest bedroom/study with access towards sun drenched roof terrace.
- Rent 2500,- excl. bills
- Deposit 2 x rent and refundable.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
- Comes with private garage.

Beautiful furnished 2 bedroom apartment with indoor balcony and garage
apartment_description:
For at least 1 year, longer preferred.
In Osdorp, a few minutes walk from the Sloterplas and with all amenities a stone's throw away, you will find this modern and well-maintained furnished 3-room apartment (80m2). The house is finished with a light wooden floor, a modern open kitchen, a fresh bathroom and sleek painted walls. Large windows in all rooms make the house wonderfully light and provide a spacious feeling.
Location
The apartment is located in Osdorp, in the middle between Stadspark Osdorp and the Botteskerkpark. Within walking distance you will find childcare, schools, various tram stops, a large shopping center, sports facilities and Theater de Meervaart. The Sloterplas is also within walking distance, so that the hiking, swimming or water sports enthusiast will undoubtedly be in the right place here. The center of Amsterdam can be reached by bicycle in about 30 minutes and via the nearby highways A10, A4 and A5 you can drive to cities such as Haarlem, Utrecht, Hoofddorp and Hilversum in a short time.
Layout
Ground floor:
Call tableau, mailboxes and communal entrance hall with stairs and elevator to the floors.
3rd floor
You reach the apartment through the covered gallery. In the hall you will find a cloakroom, neat separate toilet, cloakroom and access to all living and living areas. The living room is situated on the park side and has windows over almost the entire width, so that a generous amount of light can reach the house. A French door gives access to the balcony (12m2) over the entire width of the house. In summer you have a beautiful green view. In the front of the living room is the open kitchen with all built-in facilities. The kitchen is separated from the dining room by a bar.
Both bedrooms are located at the front of the house and look out on the gallery through large windows. The master bedroom also has a custom-made closet wall with sliding doors.
In the spacious bathroom you will find a design radiator, bathroom furniture with cupboard space, sink and double mirror cabinet and a walk-in shower with glass wall. On the other side of the hall is a large storage room with washing machine.
Outside
The house has a large covered balcony (12m2) facing south, where you can enjoy the sun in the summer. You look out on the lively street with the city park on the other side.
There is a large communal roof terrace on the fourth floor. For example, you can sit in the sun, barbecue, etc.
Particularities
- 2 bedrooms
- Open kitchen
- Indoor balcony over the entire width
- Ideal location in relation to amenities and parks
- Living area: 80 m2
- Communal roof terrace: 12 m2
- Year of construction: 2009
Conditions:
- Immediately available for at least 1 year, longer possible
- Optional private parking space in the garage for additional cost
- Preferably no pet
- Rental price: 1650,- excluding gas / electricity, TV / internet and municipal taxes.
- Deposit: 1 month rent.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.

Nicely furnished cozy 1 bedroom apartment in De Pijp
apartment_description:
For at least a year, longer preferred.
An attractive apartment where you immediately feel at home. This bright and fully furnished apartment is located in the popular district 'De Pijp' in Amsterdam Old South in a side street of the Ferdinand Bolstraat. Enjoy your cup of coffee on the balcony overlooking a lush courtyard garden. In a quiet neighborhood near the lively and bustling center of Amsterdam.
Location:
The apartment (65m²) is situated in a side street of the Ferdinand Bolstraat. A few minutes walk from shops, restaurants, the Sarphatipark, the Albert Cuyp market and public transportation.
The tram will take you to the city center, the museum quarter and to the Amstel in more than five minutes. At ten minutes from the international business center, the Zuidas and the Zuid / WTC station with a direct connection to Schiphol and Central Station. Very convenient location in relation to the roads (A10 / A9) and the Amsterdam exhibition and congress center, the RAI.
Layout:
Fully equipped living room. A new kitchen with appliances (including dishwasher and microwave). Bedroom with sufficient cupboard space, double bed and work table. Bathroom with shower, washbasin with bathroom furniture. Separate cupboard with washer-dryer. There is a laminate floor throughout the apartment. Balcony. Double glass.
Conditions:
- Rent is 1750,- exclusive g/w/e and internet.
- Refundable deposit required.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.

apartment_description:
For at least 1, longer preferred.
This fully furnished spacious 2 bedroom apartment of 80m2 is centrally located in Amstelveen.
All rooms are accessible via the spacious hall. The spacious living room and separate dining room are located on the south-east side (lots of daylight) and offer an unobstructed view on the park behind the complex.
The spacious balcony can be reached from the living room. The balcony offers a nice view of the green surroundings. Through the hallway, the bedrooms and the bathroom are accessible.
The bathroom has a walk-in shower and a washbasin with mirror and a bathroom furniture.
The kitchen is equipped with modern appliances: washing machine, dryer, large fridge freezer, oven and separate microwave oven.
There is a double bedroom with a large wardrobe and a separate single bedroom. The toilet is separate.
A small shopping center with a Lidl supermarket is in close proximity. You can choose between tram, bus or metro; these will bring you within 15 minutes to Amsterdam city-center, the Zuid-as and Schiphol. You can park your own car in front of the door for free.

- registration with the city hall is compulsory.
- minimum lease is 1 year, longer preferred.

apartment_description:
- It will be delivered unfurnished.
- Available as of today for at least 1 year, longer possible.
- Rent is 4000,- exclusive utilities.
- Two months refundable deposit required.
Modern and luxury living along the canal in the new and popular ‘Houthavens’! This spacious ground floor apartment has four large bedrooms, three bathrooms, an office and a living room with open kitchen. There is a lovely terrace on the water and private parking in the parking garage.
Layout: Access via the front garden with private entrance to the house on the ground floor. Hallway with beautiful steel door that provides access to the open kitchen and living room. The modern and luxurious kitchen is fully equipped and includes a refrigerator, freezer, induction hob with integrated extraction system, oven and a dishwasher. The living room has a beautiful wooden herringbone floor and offers a nice view on the water. From the hallway at the front a stairs will take you to the first floor where a beautiful work space is located with access to the terrace on the water. The master bedroom is located at the front and has plenty of wardrobe space and a bathroom with a shower, double sink and toilet. From the living room on the ground floor a stairs leads to the basement where the other three spacious bedrooms are situated and two full bathrooms, one of which has a bathtub. Here is also a laundry room with washing machine and dryer connections. The entire house has comfortable underfloor heating.
There are 2 parking spaces available in the parking garage that are optionally offered for € 250,00 each per month.
The Narva Island is part of the artificially created islands in the car-free Houthavens, a child-friendly city district on the IJ-river with a particularly central location. Walking distance from Amsterdam's city center with all its hotspots, such as museums, the Jordaan, Westerpark, Haarlemmerstraat and the NDSM wharf on the other side of the IJ-river.
By car you can easily reach the A10 highway and public transport is within walking distance. In addition, you can reach Central Station with a 10-minute bike ride.
In short, a very beautiful and luxurious family home in a central location on the water!

apartment_description:
For at least 1 year.
No sharing by colleagues.
Tastefully renovated and comfortable 1100 Sq Ft apartment on the first floor in Amsterdam's historic city centre, only a 5-minute walk from Amsterdam Central Station. This bright apartment has been recently renovated with great attention to detail. Part of the house dates back to around 1720, the rest was built in 1870. Beautiful high doors, wooden floors (partially original) and a spacious bathroom with bath exude luxury and tranquility.
The canals and the lively Haarlemmerstraat with its restaurants and designer boutiques are just around the corner. Despite the the neighborhood's popularity, this is a quiet street, an oasis of calm in the bustling city centre.
Layout: large and bright living room facing the street, with fully equipped open-plan kitchen. The study / guest room can be closed off from the living room, using high sliding doors. In this room, you'll find the original wooden floor, stylish finishes and pleasant lighting. In the back, far from any street sounds, is a spacious master bedroom with a long bed (6.9 Ft) and walk-in closet, a bright and beautiful wooden floor and lots of storage space. The large bathroom has underfloor heating, double sink, bathtub and a separate shower.
- Rental price is 1850,- exclusive utilities . NOT NEGOTIABLE.
- Refundable deposit required .
- Minimum lease is one year, longer preferred.

This eye catching fully furnished 2 bedrooms apartment of 62m2 lies in the centre of the Spaarndammerbuurt, 5
minutes from the city centre. It is light and airy, and boasts a
sunny southwest facing balcony.
Layout
The property door opens into the hallway, which provides
access to all areas of the flat. Access to the sunny balcony is
via the spacious double living and dining room. The open
plan kitchen that leads off from this double reception area is
equipped with all necessary kitchen utensils, such as a
dish washer. The ample master bedroom is located at the
rear of the property, and contains a king-size bed (180x210) and two wardrobes. The stylish modern bathroom benefits
from a spacious walk-in shower and washbasin. The second
(bed) room currently used as a work space houses a generous desk area, therefore serving as the perfect home office. The apartment benefits from a washing machine and
dryer. Furthermore, the apartment is fitted throughout with wooden floors and double glazed windows.
Surroundings:
The welcoming Spaarndammerstraat with its many shops,
supermarkets and restaurants is located just around the
corner. Westerpark and the Jordaan are within 5 minute
walking distance.
Public transport links are excellent, both by car, with easy
accessibility to the A10, and by public transport. Amsterdam
Central Station and Station Sloterdijk are both within a 5-10
minute cycle ride and are also accessible by bus.
Conditions:
- Immediately available for at least 1 year, longer possible.
- Rent is 1500,- exclusive utilities.
- Refundable deposit required.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.

apartment_description:
Wonderfully spacious and pleasantly divided, furnished 3-room apartment (approx. 91m2) on the 6th floor with nice balcony (approx. 10m2) facing southeast and private parking!
Do you want to live practically around the corner from the bustling 'Oud-Zuid' and still have a lot of space? Then come take a look at this bright house with unobstructed views. Within a few cycling minutes you are on the popular Hoofddorpplein, Delflandplein or Sierplein with a variety of shops and food / beverage outlets. Also near the Vondelpark, the Rembrandtpark and the Sloterplas for wonderful recreation or sports. For culture lovers, the Museumplein with various museums and the Concertgebouw can be reached within minutes, as well as the theater and conference center De Meervaart in Amsterdam Osdorp. Just a few minutes walking distance from various public transport connections (tram, train, metro and bus). Schiphol is only 7 minutes by train from Lelylaan Station. Easily accessible from the highway (A10, A9 and A4).
In short; a prime location!
LAYOUT
Sixth floor: Entrance, spacious hall with access to the various rooms, meter cupboard, storage room with connection for the washer / dryer, spacious living room/kitchen with access to the lovely, sunny balcony with unobstructed views of the greenery, open kitchen of separate equipment, well-sized bedroom and bathroom with walk-in shower, sink and toilet.
On the ground floor there is a private parking space.
PARTICULARITIES
- rental price 1750,- euro per month
- including private parking space
- excluding g/w/e and internet
- available per today
- Semi furnished. Beds will be delivered without matresses. No dining table nor washer and dryer will be delivered.
- the building has an elevator
- living surface is 91m2;

apartment_description:
It will be delivered unfurnished!
This carefully selected 4 bedrooms apartment has, among other things, a beautiful modern kitchen and 2 bathrooms. The floors are accessible via the spacious and representative entrance with 2 lifts.
Upon entering the apartment you immediately notice the high quality finish that has been implemented throughout the apartment.
• on entering you will find on the left the built-in toilet and a spacious internal storage with washing machine connection. The second floating toilet is located on the right side. On the right side of the landing are 4 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms.
• The bathrooms have a walk-in shower, a bath cabinet with double wash basins and a mirror cabinet. The last door on the right side of the landing provides access to the supply cabinet / pantry.
In the extension of the entrance are the spacious kitchen and living room.
• The kitchen is equipped with all appliances including a dishwasher, microwave, oven, refrigerator, freezer, steamer and quooker. You can cook on the cooking island where the induction cooker is installed.
• There are no radiators in the entire apartment, because the entire apartment has underfloor heating!
Area:
The complex is located on a park adjacent to the Slotervaart, the latter is ideal for pleasure cruising! By public transport (tram 1) you can quickly and easily reach the center. If you are traveling or working at Schiphol, regional transport (bus) also stops here. All major roads such as the A4, A5, A9 and A10 are within a few minutes drive. In the nearby shopping street you can go for all your daily groceries at a large supermarket, butcher, bakery or chemist. If you receive frequent visits, they may park their car for free in the area, in this part of Amsterdam there is still no parking tax!
In short, an apartment that is worth seeing is spacious, atmospheric, comfortable and luxurious! You get the nice green environment for free! If you would like to make an appointment for a viewing, call us and we will gladly guide you around!
Conditions:
- Rent is 2200,- exclusive utilities.
- Two months refundable depsoit required.
- Proof of income required.
- Minimum lease is one year, longer preferred.

apartment_description:
Sharing by max 2 non family individuals.
Available as of today for at least 1 year, longer preferred.
Rent is 1900,- exclusive utilities.
Looking for a wonderfully spacious 5-room home in Amsterdam-East, look no further! This beautiful home of approx. 116 m2 is now available for a family or max 2 non family individuals sharing. The house is equipped with three spacious bedrooms, it has a very spacious balcony at the rear and the house has a pleasant layout.
SURROUNDINGS:
The apartment has an ideal location with regard to accessibility and daily facilities. In the nearby area you will find Javaplein, Javastraat and Dapperstraat with its well-known Dappermarkt. Here you will find a diversity of nice restaurants, cafés, shops and nice boutiques.
The property is perfectly accessible both by public transport and by car. The Central Station can be reached by city bus 22 and tram 14 in about 15 minutes and these will also take you to various junctions in the city. Via exit road S114 you can reach the Ring A10 within 10 minutes by car.
LAYOUT:
The property is located on the first floor, through the neat staircase of the building, you will find the entrance of the property on the first floor. You enter the house in the central hall which gives access to all rooms in the house.
At the front of the house you will find a spacious living room with a French balcony. The living room is divided into a spacious seating area and dining area. Adjacent to the living room is the beautiful open kitchen located, equipped with a 5-burner gas stove, dishwasher, fridge / freezer and built-in oven. At the rear is the utility room and a very spacious balcony with over the inner gardens.
The house has three spacious bedrooms, a bathroom and separate toilet, all of which can be reached through the hall. The bathroom has a large shower and sink.
Furthermore, the entire house has a very maintenance-friendly floor. The house is painted in its entirety for delivery.
DETAILS:
- Living area of approximately 116m2;
- within walking distance of the pleasant Javastraat;
- Fully painted
- equipped with three spacious bedrooms;
- External storage room of approx. 6m2
- deposit is equal to two months rent and refundable.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.

Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
LOCATION
The apartment is close to Centraal Station (10 min walk), Jordaan and Spaarndammerbuurt neighbourhoods.
Tram and bus routes are also close by.
The apartment is located in a quiet section of the Jordaan, around the corner from the Noordermarkt and Lindengracht market, among other things, and near the pleasant Haarlemmerdijk with its myriad of unique shops, cafés, and restaurants, as well as The Movies cinema. Shops for your daily groceries, including a butcher’s shop, bakery and greengrocer, are within walking distance. The Haarlemmerplein and Westerpark nature park with its sports, entertainment and cultural facilities are also within easy walking distance.

Available now furnished 2 double bedrooms apartment with lake view
apartment_description:
At a nice location on the sloterplas lake at Slotermeer district in New West. Very tasteful and bright apartment with fantastic views, house-wide balcony, elevator and private storage room. Free parking in front the building!
Conditions:
- Immediately available for at least 1 year, longer possible.
- Rent is 1750,- exclusive utilities.
- Two months refundable deposit required
+ Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
Some highlights of this apartment:
• Fantastic apartment of approx. 80 m²
• Bright, attractive living room with open kitchen
• Elevator
• Full-width balcony with afternoon sun located on the west
• Luxurious bathroom with bath, TV, spacious walk-in shower, double sink and mirror heating
• Recently fully equipped with double glazing HR ++
• Dimmable LED lighting throughout the apartment Surroundings The street is located on the transition between the old and the new city, just outside the ring A10 in the Nieuw West district. The joys but not the burdens of the city! From this quiet location you are within a few minutes in the city, but also on the Ring A10. The Sloterplas is almost in your 'backyard', where you can enjoy the necessary relaxation and water sports. The Sloterpark and the Sloterparkbad are just a few minutes by bike. Around the corner is the Sloterplas beach, in warm weather you can swim, sunbathe and have a drink at the trendy Hotel Buiten. You don't have to go to the center for culture either. The Van Eesteren Pavilion was opened last autumn, the information point about the cultural-historical heritage of urban planner Cornelis van Eesteren and the starting point for guided walks and excursions. There are several exhibitions on Van Eesteren's work: post-war urban planning and architecture in Amsterdam. The northern Sloterplasoever has recently been designated a protected cityscape. For the necessary entertainment or the daily shopping you can visit the Mercatorplein, which is a short cycling distance away. The area around the Mercatorplein is rich in cafes, restaurants and shops. For daily shopping there are, among others, the Albert Heijn and many delicatessen shops. For coffee or lunch you can visit the White label Coffee, Bar Baarsch and café restaurant Zurich, or dine with a great view at Floor 17 in the Ramada hotel. The Rembrandtpark or Erasmuspark are also nearby and by bike you can easily reach the center of Amsterdam, the Jordaan, the Foodhallen or the Vondelpark. The apartment is easily accessible by car and public transport. Via the tram lines and buses on the Burgemeester Roëllstraat, via the Amsterdam Lelylaan train station or the Jan van Galen metro station. By car you are within 2 minutes on the Ring A-10 (s105). In short: a very nice and quiet place within walking distance of the Sloterplas and beautiful parks and close to all the beauty that Amsterdam has to offer.

Available now furnished 3 bedrooms apartment with lift and garage
apartment_description:
Modern and beautifully furnished apartment in a good location, just outside the Amsterdam ring highway! This apartment has 3 bedrooms and is located in a new apartment complex with elevator, a private parking space and a wonderfully spacious balcony facing west.
Conditions:
- Immediately available for at least 1 year, longer preferred.
- Rent is 1950,- exclusive utilities.
- Two months refundable deposit required.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
Layout: Arriving at the complex, you can easily park your car in your own parking space or park your bike in the storage room. Through the entrance you will take the elevator to the third floor where the apartment is located. The hallway gives access to all rooms. Living room with open kitchen, equipped with all necessary appliances, including a fridge, freezer, microwave, oven, dishwasher and an induction hob with extractor. The sliding door from floor to ceiling provides a pleasant light and nice view! From here you can step onto the nice sunny balcony! The apartment has three bedrooms. The bedroom next to the living room is nice and spacious and is currently used as a dining room. The other two bedrooms are on the other side of the apartment, one of which is equipped with a double bed and large built-in wardrobe. The other bedroom has a single bed, which can be turned into a double bed. The modern bathroom has a walk-in shower and a sink. Separate toilet and a separate room with washing machine and dryer.
Shops, schools, sports and other facilities are within walking distance. The Rembrandtpark is 200 meters away. The convenient location near public transport and the A10-West ring road make the property easily accessible. The bus stops in front of the door and a little further is the Postjesweg metro station. From there it is only 1 stop to the Lelylaan train station. You can reach the A10 ring road in a few minutes by car.
In short, a beautiful and comfortable apartment, definitely worth a visit!

Newly fully furnished 2 bedrooms apartment in IJburg
apartment_description:
Newly fully furnished 2 bedrooms apartment in IJburg immediately available.
No agency fee required nor hidden costs for the tenant.
This light and spacious 2-bedroom apartment of approx. 81 m2, with a nice view is located on the 3rd floor of a modern complex located at IJburg Amsterdam. This apartment is fully equiped with double glazing. The neighbourhood is peaceful, child-friendly and well sought after with all amenities on your doorstep. Possibility to get a parking permit or to rent a parking place inside the building.
LAY OUT
Through the shared entrance you will reach the elevator that brings you to the 3rd floor. This floor gives you access to the different apartments. The living room is located at the backside of the apartment and has lots of windows, thus giving plenty of light throughout the entire day. The open kitchen is equiped with a fridge with freezer, microwave, oven, extractor fan, 4 hub induction stove and gives you access to the balcony located at the front side of the apartment. The spacious bedroom is located at the back of the apartment and is equipped with a double bed and wardrobe. The second bedroom is located at the backside and has a single bed. The bathroom is provided with shower and washbasin with storage drawers. Seperate toilet.
There is a seperate closet with the connection for the washing machine.
On the ground floor you will find the storage box of approx. 3.3 m2.
There is a possibility to rent a parking place inside of the building. That is excluded from the rental price.
LOCATION
This apartment with 2 bedrooms is located in the area called Haven-eiland East. On walking distance you will find a diversity of supermarkets, shopping center, sport facilities, primary school, etc. IJburg gives you enough options to have a nice evening at one of the bars or restaurants in the neigborhood. The city-beach called Blijburg can be reached by walking. Ideally for a sunny day or to have a good walk!
Good connection by public transport to Central Station, approx 15 minutues with tram 26. It is very centrally located, a few minutes by car from the Ring Amsterdam A10, A4 Schiphol and A2 Utrecht, nearby Amstel or Rai for train and metro station, other public transport options (trams and buses) within 250m.
HIGHLIGHTS
Rent price is 1750,- excluding gas water and electricity
1 month deposit
Fully furnished
Available immediately
Max 2 year contract
Registration with the city hall is compulsory.

apartment_name: Available now furnished 3 bedrooms apartment near Oosterpark
apartment_description:
Modern and comfortable 3-bedrooms apartment of approx.103m2. The apartment has an elevator and a sunny balcony. The location is perfect, in the popular oosterparkbuurt, near to the Oosterpark, metro station Wibautstraat, Amstel river and De Pijp district.
Lay-out:
elevator or stairs to the second floor.
second floor; you enter and you are in a very cozy and comfortable kitchen with all the needed appliances
large and bright living room. On this floor there is a guest toilet and quite some storage. Throughout this floor you will find a an oak-wooden floor.
third floor gives access to the second part of the apartment. Three good size bedrooms. Master has a sunny balcony.
the modern bathroom has a bathtub, separate shower and toilet.
the whole apartment has been refurbished in 2017, including fully modern and refurbished bathroom and toilet in high quality, and new robust doors, door frames. The bathroom has floor heating and mirror heating.
Located in a quiet street in the popular Osterparkbuurt. The environment can be characterized by loads of popular bars/terraces and restaurants. The pijp is within walking distance as well as beukenplein, the dappermarkt and the oosterpark.
the apartment is well-served by public transport with excellent bus-, tram- and metro connections. The metro station wibautstraat can be reached in just a 2 minute walk and is connected to all amsterdam metro lines.
by car the a1 and a2 are easy accessible via the wibautstraat and s112.
Special details:
- fully furnished apartment in a modern building
- sunny balcony
- separate storage
- elevator
Conditions:
- immediately available for at least 1 year, longer possible
- rent is 2200,- exclusive utilities.
- refundable deposit required.
- registration with the city hall is mandatory

Furnished 2 good bedrooms apartment near Bijlmer Arena
apartment_description:
For rent as of today for at least 1 year, longer preferred, apartment located in Amsterdam Southeast near Bijlmer Arena and Ganzenhoef stations. Affordable living in a green environment in Amsterdam? Then this playful 2 well sized bedrooms apartment located on the 1st floor of the complex is for you! It features a sunny balcony is located on the 1st floor of a well-maintained complex. This house is conveniently located for shops, schools and public transport. The metro (53) will take you to the center of Amsterdam in 15 minutes! There are various facilities in the vicinity such as the AMC, Ikea, the Amsterdam Arena and Arenaboulevard with Ziggo Dome, Pathé cinema, but also the Amsterdamse Poort shopping center, the Nelson Mandelapark and the "Gaasperplas" nature and recreation area. For daily shopping you can go to shopping center Ganzenpoort or de Kameleon. The highways a1, a2, a9 and the a10 are quickly accessible. There is a handy storage room on the ground floor.
A small tour:
Entrance, spacious hall and toilet. Through the spacious hall you reach the spacious and bright living room with laminate flooring and sliding panels. From this living room you enter the balcony located on the southeast. The kitchen is equipped with a 4-burner gas stove with oven, dishwasher, refrigerator and spacious built-in cupboard with an Intergas Combi boiler (2018). The 2 bedrooms have a laminate floor. There is a separate toilet and the bathroom has a shower, towel radiator, washing machine connection and washbasin with mirror. The balcony is located on the southeast.
- living space approx. 72 m2
- storage room on the ground floor
- plenty of free parking
- closed entrance and intercom system.
- the rental price is 1400, -excluding gas and light.
- refundable deposit required.
- registration with the city hall is compulsory.

Furnished 1 bedroom apartment in De Pijp for 6 months
apartment_description:
Nice one-bedroom apartment located in the 'Pijp': available for a period of 6 months!
Apartment
The apartment is on the first floor at the front of the building. Entry into the living room.
Living room with seating and dining area. Open kitchen with all necessary appliances. Bedroom with double bed and wardrobe. Bathroom with shower, toilet and sink. Separate cabinet with washer/dryer. The apartment has been renovated just a few years ago and is fully and completely furnished.
Environment
The location is central; in the middle of the bustling 'Pijp', within walking distance of 'Oud Zuid' and steps away from, the Albert Cuyp market and the beautifully landscaped Sarphatipark. Around the corner are the 'Marie Heinekenplein', 'Pilsvogel' and several large shopping areas such as the 'Ferdinand Bolstraat', the 'Van Woustraat' and 'Ceintuurbaan'.
Conditions
Available per Dec 1st.
- Maximum rental period 06 months.
- Furnished. Rent € 1.500 excluding utilities. A fixed amount of € 100,- per month will be charged for gas, water, electricity, TV, WiFi.
- Deposit € 3.200,-.

Luxurious house near Vondelpark 5 bedrooms 2 bathrooms and terrace
apartment_description:
Luxurious and beautiful 5 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms 230m² house for rent nearby Vondelpark with garden and rooftop terrace.
Neighborhood:
This amazing house is located next to Vondelpark and within walking distance from the concert hall, PC Hooftstraat and Museumplein. In this prestigious residential area is also lively with many amazing restaurants and the Concert Hall nearby as well as Rijksmuseum, Conservatorium Hotel and the shopping street P. C. Hooftstraat with many high end and luxury brands.
Layout:
The entrance is in a beautiful library-like hallway with a wooden floor and beautiful bookcases from the floor to the ceiling. You can take the stairs down to the amazing big living kitchen with a bar and seating area or you can take the stairs upstairs to the first living room with fireplace and separate study. The kitchen downstairs gives access to a cozy outside area. Upstairs on the first floor you find 2 bedrooms with one bathroom with jacuzzi, toilet, double washing basin and a big walk in shower. One of the bedrooms has a spectacular walk in closet. Also this floor has a separate laundry area. On the next floor you find two very large bedrooms, one with a private bathroom with a bathtub. Also there is a fifth bedroom available on this floor. As finishing touch: this amazing house has a spacious rooftop with a spectacular view.
Due to the fact that there are two formal addresses on this object, you are also able to rent it partially as a business, and partially as a residence.
Features:
* 5 bedrooms
* 2 bathrooms
* near Vondelpark
* indefinite contract
* minimum rental period is 12 months
* possibility to rent it as a combined business AND private address
* rent is 6000,- exclusive g/w/e and internet
There is potentially a possibility for 2 parking permits.

Furnished 3 bedrooms waterfront house with garage
apartment_description:
Unique waterfront house of approx.118 m2 with a private front door entry, 3 bedrooms, two floors, living room directly on the water, a lovely sunny covered terrace, a private jetty and a covered parking garage in the same building! All windows are facing to the South.
All the windows facing to the south, making this property very special indeed. The living room is overlooking a beautiful canal, while the bedrooms are slightly above street level. A unique place surrounded by water and stunning views of the canal filled with all-day long sunshine.
Rental conditions:
- 2250 with parking space (no service costs), exclusive utilities.
- Deposit 1.5x month
- House is delivered furnished.
Layout:
You enter the property through your private front door, which gives direct access to the spacious and bright hallway with separate toilet, 3 large bedrooms and a large bathroom. The modern bathroom has a bath, shower, double sink and toilet, all were renovated in 2017. Next to the bathroom there is a practical storage room with plenty of space for the washing machine a dryer and other household items to store.
A floor below is the living room with a modern open kitchen, equipped with a combi oven, dishwasher, ceramic hob, granite counter top. Additionally, under the stairwell there is a practical cupboard with a separate door. Directly from the living room you can access a large beautiful South-facing terrace and a private jetty. The jetty is completely private, and you can moor a boat of up to 12 meters here. You can sail either towards IJmeer or towards downtown Amsterdam, as well as the Blijburg beach. The house has fantastic views over the water through the many windows.
In the basement you will find an additional spacious storage room, with plenty of space to store bikes and other equipment. Here you will also find your personal car parking space (in a covered garage), being offered together with the property (not sold or rented separately). Therefore, the asking price is incl. the parking lot.
Surroundings:
IJburg a modern, but cozy island on the east side of Amsterdam. It is one of the youngest neighborhoods in Amsterdam and is characterized by the contemporary varied construction, beautiful recreation areas and plenty of water masses surrounding it from all sides. This is the place to be in the summer, when all Amsterdam rushes to its Blijburg beach and many cafes and restaurants. In your immediate surrounding you will find the children friendly Theeo van Gogh park, with the Diemerpark being a 5-minute bike ride away. The area is packed with various restaurants,
cafes, grocery stores, health & beauty establishments and (water) sport clubs. IJburg has one of the best high schools in Amsterdam and plenty of nurseries.
Accessibility:
The accessibility is excellent access to both the A10 and A1 highways, as well as a main street (IJBurglaan) taking you to downtown in Amsterdam in under 10 minutes. The car can be parked at the covered garage directly under the apartment building, included in the asking price. Public transport connections are also very good with tram line 26 taking you to Central Station in under 20 minutes.
Particularities:
- Private jetty, directly adjacent to the terrace
- Parking space in a covered garage, directly under the house
- Private front door entry on ground level (very handy for unloading groceries)
- 3 bedrooms with a huge master bedroom
- Living room slightly above water level, providing for an amazing sight
- Terrace towards the South directly on the water
- Directly on the waterway - open connection to the IJmeer and downtown Amsterdam

Furnished 2 bedrooms apartment with lift terrace and garage
apartment_description:
Safe living in a high class apartment with a southwest facing balcony and panoramic views on the water, excluding a private parking spot in the garage.
Located close to the center of Amsterdam at the Eastern Docklands a high class sunny three rooms apartmen. The apartment includes a covered private parking, private storage box and a common bicycle shed.
Characteristic of this building is its modern design.
Division; entrance, hall, large living with door to 7 square meters balcony, open kitchen with all amenities, master bedroom, second large bedroom, separate lavatory, luxurious bathroom with double bathroom cabinet and shower. The apartment is fully furnished and in perfect condition. Ideal apartment for safe and high class living in sought-after area for professionals / a couple.
This spacious 2 bedrooms apartment offers a great opportunity to enjoy this convenient neighborhood only 10 minutes away from Amsterdam City Center.
Neighborhood:
Located near the -IJ-, close to Central Station and the KNSM Island. The combination of distinctive architecture, living near the water and the number of restaurants, cafés, schools and trendy shops makes living in this area very pleasant.
Details:
- Size of the property: approximately 100m2
- Number of bedrooms: 2
- Number of bathrooms: 1
- Quality of public transportation: very good
-Tram lines 10 and 26 and bus lines 22, 48 and 65
- Construction year of the building: 1998
- Flooring: Laminate
- Separate toilet
High class bathroom
- Balcony (facing south west) with city view
- Communal bicycle storage facility
- Video-intercom
- 2 Elevators
+ Storage: private box
- Private parking
- Rent 1900,- per month excluding g/w/e and internet
Refundable deposit required equal to 2 months rent.
- Private parking lot in underneath garage is optional and costs around 150,- monthly.
- Registration with the city hall is compulsory.
